Explanation of Architecture
🔹 1. End Users
Users access media using browser

Example:

http://<EC2-Public-IP>/image.jpg
🔹 2. EC2 Instance (Web Server)
Hosts Apache (httpd) web server
Acts as a secure middle layer
Fetches media from S3 and serves to users
🔹 3. IAM Role (Security Layer)
Attached to EC2 instance
Provides secure access to S3 bucket
No need to store credentials manually

👉 This is the most important security part

🔹 4. Private S3 Bucket
Stores media files (images/videos)
Public access is completely blocked
Only EC2 can access via IAM role
🔹 5. Media Delivery
EC2 copies media files from S3
Stores them in /var/www/html
Serves files via HTTP
🔥 Key Features of This Architecture

✅ Secure media storage
✅ No public access to S3
✅ IAM-based authentication
✅ Controlled access via EC2
✅ Simple and cost-effective
